Date: 0/0/1949
Source: Dictionary of Slang Addenda
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 1035
Edition:
Quote: Drag the chain. To be at the rear in a race or in a game (of, e.g., cribbage): New Zealand: C. 20. Niall Alexander, letter of Oct. 22, 1939, `The ploughman's term to designate his slow horse that does not keep its chains tight'.
Notes: 1939 in 1949 Partridge Dict Slang Addenda 1035

Date: 0/0/1951
Source: Personal Communication
Author: PROF. W. CAMERON
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: A trampers' term applied to those who go very slowly (uphill).
